  "market_context": "On Tuesday 14 Oct '25, NQ1! daily candle did not support upside expansion due to a large opposing run, but the 4-hour and hourly candles formed candle 3 continuation structures aligned for an upside move toward the daily open near 24,900.",
  "key_observation": "Even though the daily candle opposes the bullish bias, the 4-hour and hourly time frames form aligned candle 3 expansions, which can support a conservative lower time frame long back toward the daily open or intraday highs.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Assess the daily candle and conclude it does not support upside expansion due to a large opposing run, so target is limited to the daily open or intraday highs.",
    "Step 2: Check the 4-hour candle, which is bearish (open, small wick, trading lower) and does not support expansion higher, requiring a wait for a new HTF candle at 10 a.m.",
    "Step 3: Check the hourly candle, which initially does not support expansion but then forms a candle 2 closure with a large reversal wick that can be framed for upside.",
    "Step 4: Wait for change in state of delivery on the lower time frame paired with the hourly candle 2 closure to confirm the long entry.",
    "Step 5: Identify candle 3 forming around 24,775–24,800 on the 5-minute, aligned with the 4-hour candle 3, supporting the bullish lower time frame swing.",
    "Step 6: Take conservative targets since the setup opposes the daily candle direction, aiming back toward the daily open near 24,900."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price expanded higher off the candle 3 reaching back toward the daily open near 24,900, then consolidated as anticipated given the daily headwind.",
  "lessons": "Always check higher time frames for trend alignment before taking lower time frame setups. Great LTF structure against the HTF trend rarely works out; when HTF opposes, take more conservative targets back to the daily open.",
